## Q19. What is RDP Shortpath?
RDP Shortpath establishes a UDP-based transport between client and session host. It improves latency and reliability. It starts with TCP reverse connect, switches to UDP if available, otherwise falls back to TCP. Default UDP port is 3390.
---
## Q20. How many ways can RDP Shortpath be configured?
Two ways → Managed Network (private connection like VPN/ExpressRoute) and Public Network (internet-based).
---
## Q21. UDP connection between session host & client happens in which scenario?
Public Network using STUN (direct UDP) or TURN (relayed UDP).
---
